result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley L Sheehan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ashley L Sheehan is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Ashley L Sheehan was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Court advises defendant of count 2/max. penalties.  Defendant pleads no contest.  Plea Colloquy. Court finds defendant's waiver of her constitutional rights & plea done knowingly & voluntarily, accepts plea and finds defendant guilty, dismiss count 1.  Sentence to 10 days in the Pepin County Jail, report 1/25 at 3 p.m. with credit for 1 day served; waive costs.  Advised of appeal rights.

Defendant Ashley L Sheehan in court with attorney Patrick William Waters.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agreement reached.  Defendant will plead to count 2, count 1 will be DRI, 10 days jail, request costs be waived, not employed.
